shared_text:
California Department of Education
June 1 at 3:42 PM ¬∑

State Superintendent Tony Thurmond today responded to the death of George Floyd by calling on communities across the state and nation to take action to dismantle institutional racism and inequities in public schools.

He also invited students, educators, families, and partners to participate in an upcoming series of honest, courageous conversations that can help inform the work ahead.

Read more: https://www.cde.ca.gov/nr/ne/yr20/yr20rel40.asp

Share your voice and ideas for promoting racial justice: createracialjustice@gmail.com.

post_text:
I wanted to give you some information regarding free or reduced-cost school meals. This information may not apply to you but I am erring on the side of casting a wide net to help make sure we don‚Äôt miss anyone. If your financial situation has changed as we grapple with the impact of COVID-19, please know you can apply for free or reduced-cost school meals. The website with applications and income guidelines can be found at the link below.

http://www.schoolnutritionandfitness.com/index.php?sid=1711090011155483&page=lunchapps

We distribute school meals at New Brighton, Soquel Elementary, and the Emerald Bay Apartment Buildings each weekday from 10:00 - 12:00. You can pick up a hard copy application at those locations during food distribution. You can also drop off completed applications there. If you need a different time to turn in an application please call the district office at (831) 464-5630 to arrange a drop-off time.

post_text:
Friday, October 25, 2019 (12:30 p.m.)

Dear SUESD Parents, Families, & Staff,
It appears likely that another round of PG&E's planned Public Safety Power Shutoffs (PSPS) will take place in our area this weekend. I want to keep you informed on how this will impact SUESD Schools. Please rest assured that student safety will always be the top factor considered when making any decisions of this nature. As of this moment, we are planning to have a regular school day on Monday, October 28, 2019. We will, however, be monitoring the situation very closely over the weekend. I will send you updates over the weekend with the latest information. If it becomes necessary to cancel school on Monday, I will send you that information as soon as humanly possible. The uncertain nature of the shutdowns is undoubtedly frustrating. I empathize with the challenging nature of childcare and work schedules and how this uncertainty complicates things even further. We'll get through this together, again. Thanks for your cooperation and patience.
Sincerely,
Scott Turnbull
SUESD Superintendent
text:
Friday, October 25, 2019 (12:30 p.m.)

Dear SUESD Parents, Families, & Staff,
It appears likely that another round of PG&E's planned Public Safety Power Shutoffs (PSPS) will take place in our area this weekend. I want to keep you informed on how this will impact SUESD Schools. Please rest assured that student safety will always be the top factor considered when making any decisions of this nature. As of this moment, we are planning to have a regular school day on Monday, October 28, 2019. We will, however, be monitoring the situation very closely over the weekend. I will send you updates over the weekend with the latest information. If it becomes necessary to cancel school on Monday, I will send you that information as soon as humanly possible. The uncertain nature of the shutdowns is undoubtedly frustrating. I empathize with the challenging nature of childcare and work schedules and how this uncertainty complicates things even further. We'll get through this together, again. Thanks for your cooperation and patience.
Sincerely,
Scott Turnbull
SUESD Superintendent

Welcome the newest SUESD Board Member!

The Soquel Union Elementary School District‚Äôs Board of Trustees appointed Jennifer Izant Gonzales to their vacant Board Seat at a regular Board Meeting on May 1, 2019. After a rigorous interview process in open session, the Board unanimously selected her. Mrs. Izant Gonzales is a Teacher on Special Assignment at the Santa Cruz County Office of Education and proud parent of a Main Street Elementary School Student. She is heavily involved in her community and expressed the following as her reason for seeking a Board Seat, ‚ÄúAs a lifelong learner, public school educator, and community supporter, I am dedicated to improving public education for the students of Santa Cruz County. I look forward to being part of the cohesive SUESD School Board team which supports the vision of the district to work as a community to ensure achievement for all of our students.‚Äù Her term lasts through November of 2020.

post_text:
Dear SUESD Parents & Families,

It's here! Tomorrow, Wednesday, August 22, 2018, is the first day back to school for students in our district's schools. Every year in a young person's development is precious, and we take it as an honor to educate your child. As you know, this is our big year for building those new classrooms! We are making every attempt to limit the impact of construction on instruction. Still, the work is bound to impact the start of the school day and dismissal. In this regard, I merely ask that we all give ourselves a little extra cushion time-wise at drop-off and pick-up and have as much patience as possible. School and District Staff will be out and about tomorrow doing everything we can to make the start of this school year a smooth one. Have a great first day tomorrow.

Sincerely,

Scott Turnbull, SUESD Superintendent

post_text:
Dear SUESD Parents & Families,

Welcome to the 2018-19 School Year in Soquel Union Elementary School District. We are looking forward to another fantastic year of learning. I wanted to remind you to please complete the Back To School forms for your child(ren) if you have not already. These forms were sent to you via the parent portal. These forms will not be available on paper. Having full information for all of our students is imperative to student safety and record keeping. We will not be able to release student class placement until these forms are complete and the beginning of the year is approaching quickly. If you need any assistance please contact your child's school or contact us here at the District Office.

First day of school is August 22, 2018!

Sincerely,

Scott Turnbull
SUESD Superintendent
sturnbull@suesd.org

Services are provided in the school environment. Assist the certificated teacher in all aspects of classroom processes, including facilitation of student social interaction and small group instruction. Employees in this classification receive general supervision within a standard framework of policies and procedures while working in the school environment.

post_text:
Sunday, May 6, 2018

Dear NBMS Staff & Parents,

We just became aware of a water leak underneath New Brighton's parking lot closest to the district office and Monterey Park. We must shut down the impacted water line to repair it first thing tomorrow morning. The restrooms & water fountains that will be available tomorrow are in the PAC and the Gym. Bringing a bottle of drinking water is advisable. I apologize for this inconvenience. We will still prepare school lunches since this line does not provide water to the New Brighton Kitchen. All school activities will proceed as usual. This message is just a "heads-up" so everyone knows what to expect tomorrow. Thanks for your patience and understanding.

Sincerely,

Scott Turnbull
Superintendent
text:
Sunday, May 6, 2018

Dear NBMS Staff & Parents,

We just became aware of a water leak underneath New Brighton's parking lot closest to the district office and Monterey Park. We must shut down the impacted water line to repair it first thing tomorrow morning. The restrooms & water fountains that will be available tomorrow are in the PAC and the Gym. Bringing a bottle of drinking water is advisable. I apologize for this inconvenience. We will still prepare school lunches since this line does not provide water to the New Brighton Kitchen. All school activities will proceed as usual. This message is just a "heads-up" so everyone knows what to expect tomorrow. Thanks for your patience and understanding.

Sincerely,

Scott Turnbull
Superintendent
